#: front-page.php:487
msgid "Live"
msgstr "Moʻui"

#: front-page.php:365
msgid "Browse Meetings"
msgstr "Vakai ki he Ngaahi Fakataha"

#: front-page.php:368
msgid "All public meetings — boards, commissions, and councils — in one calendar. Filter by topic, council, or date. AI-generated summaries explain what's on the agenda."
msgstr "Ko e ngaahi fakataha fakasōsaieti kotoa — ngaahi pooti, komisoni, mo e ngaahi kautaha — ʻi he kalena pe taha. Fakalelei ʻaki kaveinga, kautaha, pe ʻaho. Ko e ngaahi hōfanga AI ʻoku fakamatala ko e hā ʻi he lāunga."

#: front-page.php:405
msgid "Council Profiles"
msgstr "Ngaahi Fakamatala Kautaha"

#: front-page.php:408
msgid "Learn what each board and commission actually does — in plain language. See who sits on the board, upcoming meetings, open seats, and how to participate."
msgstr "Ako ko e hā ʻoku fai ʻe he pooti mo e komisoni kotoa — ʻi lea mahino. Sio ko hai ʻoku nofo ʻi he pooti, ngaahi fakataha ka hoko, ngaahi nofoʻanga tatala, mo e founga ke kau ai."

#: front-page.php:445
msgid "Get Alerts"
msgstr "Maʻu Ngaahi Fakalāloa"

#: front-page.php:448
msgid "Subscribe to topics or specific councils. Get email alerts when meetings are scheduled — before it's too late to participate."
msgstr "Lēkooti ki he ngaahi kaveinga pe ngaahi kautaha fakaʻutuʻutu. Maʻu ngaahi fakalāloa ʻimeli ʻi he taimi ʻoku fakamālohi ai ʻa e ngaahi fakataha — kimuʻa pea vela ʻa e taimi ke kau ai."

#: front-page.php:489
msgid "Guides & Compliance"
msgstr "Ngaahi Hūfanga mo e Tatau"

#: front-page.php:492
msgid "Step-by-step civic action guides plus compliance tools for agencies — Sunshine Law, public records, accessibility, and public participation best practices."
msgstr "Ngaahi hūfanga ngāue fakafonua feʻunga mo e ngāue tatau maʻa e ngaahi kautaha — Lao Saʻisinisini, ngaahi lēkooti fakasōsaieti, mālohi kumi, mo e ngaahi founga lelei taha ke kau ai ʻa e kakai."

#: front-page.php:511
msgid "What we believe"
msgstr "Ko e meʻa ʻoku mau tui ki ai"

#: front-page.php:513
msgid "Information access is a community right"
msgstr "Ko e mālohi kumi fakamatala ko e totonu ʻo e kakai"

#: front-page.php:516
msgid "Every resident deserves to know what decisions are being made that affect their community — in language they can understand, at a time when they can still participate."
msgstr "ʻOku totonu ke ʻilo ʻe he kakai kotoa pē ko e hā ngaahi fili ʻoku fai ʻoku ueʻi honau kominiti — ʻi lea ʻoku nau mahino ki ai, ʻi he taimi te nau lava ai ke kau."

#: front-page.php:534
msgid "Strictly nonpartisan"
msgstr "Taʻe fakapāti aupito"

#: front-page.php:535
msgid "Civi.Me does not endorse candidates, parties, or positions on any issue. We present facts: what a bill does, who submitted it, when the hearing is. We provide tools and templates — never talking points."
msgstr "ʻOku ʻikai fakafaingamālie ʻe Civi.Me ha kau taukaveinga, pāti, pe tuʻunga ki ha meʻa. ʻOku mau hāʻele ʻa e moʻoni: ko e hā ʻoku fai ʻe he tohi lao, ko hai naʻe tukuange, ko ʻenefē ʻa e fanongo. ʻOku mau foaki ngāue mo e ngaahi sipinga — taʻefoki ha ngaahi uenga."

#: front-page.php:549
msgid "Everyone is included — no exceptions"
msgstr "Ko e kakai kotoa pē ʻoku kau — ʻikai ha fakakehe"

#: front-page.php:550
msgid "We use \"residents\" — not \"citizens.\" We support all 15 languages recognized by Hawaii's Office of Language Access. We build for mobile and include a phone line for people who don't have a smartphone at all."
msgstr "ʻOku mau fakaʻaongaʻi \"kakai nofo\" — ʻikai \"kau pisinisi.\" ʻOku mau poupou ki he ngaahi lea 15 kotoa pē ʻoku ʻiloʻi ʻe he Ofisi Lea ʻo Hawaii. ʻOku mau langa maʻa e fōni mo e laine fōni maʻa e kakai ʻoku ʻikai ha fōni lalafo."

#: front-page.php:561
msgid "Cultural respect is not optional"
msgstr "Ko e fakaʻapaʻapa fakaʻikuna ʻoku ʻikai fakaʻatā"

#: front-page.php:562
msgid "Native Hawaiian sovereignty is a living issue, not history. We frame civic participation as community engagement — not blind deference to government structures."
msgstr "Ko e māfimafi ʻo e kakai tuʻi ʻo Hawaii ko e meʻa moʻui, ʻikai ko e hisitōlia. ʻOku mau fakaʻaongaʻi ʻa e kau fakafonua ko e ngāue kominiti — ʻikai ko e fai anga taʻeʻilo ki he ngaahi fakatuʻutuʻu puleʻanga."

#: front-page.php:573
msgid "Open source and community-built"
msgstr "Mālohi ʻata mo e langa ʻe he kominiti"

#: front-page.php:574
msgid "Civi.Me's code is public on GitHub from day one. Civic infrastructure should be open to inspection, contribution, and community ownership. If we ever make a decision you disagree with, you can see exactly why — and you can help us do better."
msgstr "Ko e kōtoa ʻo Civi.Me ʻoku fakasōsaieti ʻi GitHub talu mei he ʻaho ʻuluaki. ʻOku totonu ke tatala ʻa e fakatuʻutuʻu fakafonua ki he sio, tokoni, mo e pule ʻe he kominiti. Kapau ʻoku mau fili ha meʻa ʻoku ke fehangahangai mo ia, ʻoku ke lava ke sio ko e hā ʻaupito — mo e lava ke ke tokoni kiate kimautolu ke fai lelei aʻu ange."

#: front-page.php:589
msgid "Join us"
msgstr "Kau mai"

#: front-page.php:591
msgid "Help build civic infrastructure for Hawaii"
msgstr "Tokoni ke langa ʻa e fakatuʻutuʻu fakafonua maʻa Hawaii"

#: front-page.php:594
msgid "Civi.Me is open source and community-driven. Whether you're a developer, a civic advocate, or just someone who cares — there's a place for you."
msgstr "Ko Civi.Me ʻoku mālohi ʻata mo e tataki ʻe he kominiti. Pe ko e tokotaha ngāue tekinolosia, ko e poupou fakafonua, pe ko e tokotaha ʻoku tokanga — ʻoku ʻi ai ha feituʻu maʻau."

#: front-page.php:607
msgid "View on GitHub"
msgstr "Sio ʻi GitHub"

#: front-page.php:610
msgid "Get in touch"
msgstr "Feʻofoʻofani"

